                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_kʼūtʼi" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><form type="lemma"><orth>kʼūtʼi</orth></form><usg><lang/></usg><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>скорченный</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>writhed</q></abv:tr></sense><etym xml:lang="ru">Усвоено из картвельских языков; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>kʼutʼi</w> <gloss><q>безногий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><lang/> <w>k’ut’a</w> <gloss><q>короткий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><w>da-k’unt’ua</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>k’unt’va</w> <gloss><q>скорчиться</q></gloss></mentioned>. Картвельские слова, в свою очередь, связаны, вероятно, с <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*ku(n)ta-</w> <gloss><q>короткий</q></gloss></mentioned>; см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼ0yndæg"/>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It was acquired from Kartvelian languages; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>kʼutʼi</w> <gloss><q>leg-less</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><lang/> <w>k’ut’a</w> <gloss><q>short</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><w>da-k’unt’ua</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>k’unt’va</w> <gloss><q>writhe</q></gloss></mentioned>. Kartvelian words, in their turn, are probably related to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*ku(n)ta-</w> <gloss><q>short</q></gloss></mentioned>; see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kʼ0yndæg"/>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>